OL,3,CBereaved mother shines light on thread-
OL,4,Cbare probation service
OL,6,FA 110-page Serious Further Offences
OL,7,Freview into how the probation service
OL,8,Fmanaged Boulton in the period before
OL,9,Fthe murders has now been shared with
OL,10,FBethany and DJ's family.
OL,12,FBoulton had been assessed by the
OL,13,Fprobation service as posing a medium
OL,14,Frisk to Bethany and her children, and
OL,15,Fthat assessment remained the same
OL,16,Fthroughout the review period, despite
OL,17,Fthe fact Boulton was convicted and
OL,18,Fsentenced for further offences against
OL,19,FBethany and her mother.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/12
