OL,6,FCaroline said after this happened, she
OL,7,Fwas also attacked by Boulton, and he
OL,8,Fattacked Bethany again too. Despite
OL,9,Fthis, the assessment of the risk he
OL,10,Fposed to Bethany did not change and
OL,11,Fthere was no reference to the risk
OL,12,Fposed to herself - a finding Caroline
OL,13,Fdescribed as "just unbelievable".
OL,15,F"I think you could ask any member of
OL,16,Fthe public to read his background and
OL,17,Fthen say to them, 'what would you risk
OL,18,Fthem as?'
OL,20,F"I would say 100% of people would say
OL,21,Fthat would be a high risk person."
