OL,3,CBereaved mother shines light on thread-
OL,4,Cbare probation service
OL,6,F"On behalf of all the agencies
OL,7,Finvolved, we apologise for the
OL,8,Ffailings in this case. We have already
OL,9,Ftaken action to prevent a tragedy like
OL,10,Fthis from happening again, including
OL,11,Fimproving information sharing between
OL,12,Fprobation, police and children's
OL,13,Fservices, and strengthening domestic
OL,14,Fabuse training for staff."
OL,16,FMartin Jones, HM Chief Inspector of
OL,17,FProbation, told ITV News Calendar that
OL,18,Fhis assessments of probation services
OL,19,Fso far suggest around two thirds of
OL,20,Foffenders are not being managed
OL,21,Fproperly.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@ZO]
