OL,3,CBereaved mother shines light on thread-
OL,4,Cbare probation service
OL,6,F"The probation service does have a
OL,7,Fvery difficult job to do, it's dealing
OL,8,Fwith a caseload of almost a quarter of
OL,9,Fa million people. We need to make sure
OL,10,Fthere is government investment for the
OL,11,Flong term to ensure they can cope with
OL,12,Ftheir growing caseload."
OL,14,FMr Jones said failings within the
OL,15,Fservice are often because there are
OL,16,Ftoo few staff, with not enough
OL,17,Fexperience, managing too many cases -
OL,18,Fwhich leads to things being missed.
