OL,6,F"It must be possible to join up
OL,7,Finformation on people that may
OL,8,Frepresent a significant risk to the
OL,9,Fpublic."
OL,11,FCaroline said numerous red flags were
OL,12,Fraised about Boulton's behaviour, but
OL,13,Fnothing was done.
OL,15,FShe said: "He threatened our family
OL,16,Fmultiple times. He'd attacked me and
OL,17,FBethany multiple times. He told people
OL,18,Fwhat he was going to, he made comments
OL,19,Fthat he wanted to wipe out the
OL,20,Fbloodline. He told probation services
OL,21,F(of his) hatred for DJ.
